  "title": "PROJECT MANAGER - ELECTRICAL",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Lead and manage a team of supervisors, technicians, subcontractors, and vendors to deliver projects on time and within scope.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the preparation, review, and submission of shop drawings, as-built drawings, and material take-offs.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate and monitor site activities, proactively resolve technical and operational issues, and represent the company in meetings with contractors and stakeholders.</li>\n  <li>Track project progress, ensure quality standards are met, and manage material usage to align with project requirements and schedules.</li>\n  <li>Enforce strict compliance with workplace safety, health, and environmental regulations on-site.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Electrical Engineering or equivalent qualification.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 8 years of proven project management experience in electrical works within construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of MEP design and coordination.</li>\n  <li>Excellent leadership, problem-solving, and communication skills.</li>\n</ul>",
